Components
----------

This Work is composed of several cooperating components:

  - actuator-min (Rust, std library only) — reference egress actuator with
    anti-replay journal and 32-byte frame ABI.
  - dashboard (Python, stdlib http.server) — analyst-facing observational
    dashboard with optional LLM-backed context analysis.
  - installer / deploy (POSIX shell + systemd) — production deployment
    scripts, boot-time integrity guard, and systemd unit definitions.
  - adversarial (POSIX shell) — adversarial testing harness (phase 4).

Third-party components
----------------------

The Rust `actuator-min` binary depends solely on the Rust standard library
and has no external Cargo dependencies.

The Python `dashboard` component dynamically loads optional third-party
libraries when present:

  - anthropic (MIT, Copyright Anthropic, PBC) — optional, for LLM context
  - openai (MIT, Copyright OpenAI) — optional, for LLM context

These dependencies are imported with graceful degradation if absent.

